verbose_text: Synthetic SOD mimetics such as nitroxides (tempol) and compound M40403 efficiently decreased hydroxyl radical production and tissue inflammation and injury and also reduced neutrophil infiltration at the site of inflammation in addition to protecting against cell death and loss of mitochondrial content in articular cartilage after mechanical overload [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: SOD mimetics such as nitroxides (tempol) and compound M40403 efficiently decreased hydroxyl radical production and tissue inflammation and injury
